  "text": "As displayed in Table 1 , adult-informant reports were modestly associated with child self-perceptions of competence. Children's explicit and implicit self-perceptions of competence were uncorrelated; however, variable relations are common among implicit and explicit measures of a construct, depending on moderators like social desirability [CITATION_1] . Table 2 contains analyses showing that children with ADHD and TD children did not differ in their explicit self-reports of social or behavioral competence. Adult informants rated children with ADHD as having lower social and behavioral competence, relative to TD children. As such, independentsamples t tests suggested that children with ADHD had larger explicit social and behavioral PIB scores than TD children, as expected.",
